5000|$|The Convention on the Limitation Period in the International <b>Sale</b> <b>of</b> <b>Goods</b> (the [...] "Limitation Convention") is {{a uniform}} law treaty {{prepared}} by the United Nations Commission on International Trade Law (UNCITRAL). It deals with the prescription of actions relating to contracts for the international <b>sale</b> <b>of</b> <b>goods</b> due {{to the passage of}} time.|$|R
